Security Infrastructure

Purpose: Low-level security primitives and services that are independent of any specific business module.

What belongs here:
- Password hashing utilities (bcrypt, Argon2, HMAC-SHA256 wrappers)
- Token generation and validation (JWT, opaque tokens, refresh tokens)
- Encryption and decryption helpers (AES, RSA wrappers)
- Secure random number and UUID generation
- API key generation and validation
- Request signature verification
- Secure string comparison (constant-time)
- Certificate and key loading utilities

Do NOT place here:
- Business authorization rules (those belong in services)
- Feature-specific auth flows (those belong in modules/auth/)
- WebBroker-dependent auth middleware (those belong in shared/middleware/)

